  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "EbUKoyS+3iCiC3Gki/07f6kmPsI=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "The revision history panel is rendered by Connect (not the editor) when the user clicks the history button. It lives inside `#document-editor-context` in the DOM, which means the editor component has no React-level control over its appearance.\n\nTo style it, use CSS in the project's `style.css` scoped to the document type:\n\n```css\n#document-editor-context[data-document-type=\"your/document-type\"] {\n  background-color: #1e1e2e;\n  color: #cdd6f4;\n}\n```\n\nKey CSS targets inside the revision history panel:\n\n- `.bg-slate-50` / `[class*=\"bg-gray-50\"]` \u2014 header pills (DOC ID, BRANCH, scope)\n- `article` \u2014 revision cards\n- `.rounded-md.bg-slate-50` \u2014 timeline content area\n- `.border-slate-100` \u2014 timeline left border\n- `h2.bg-slate-50` \u2014 day separator headers\n- `.text-gray-900`, `.text-stone-300`, `.text-gray-600` \u2014 text colors\n- `.border-gray-200`, `.bg-white` \u2014 borders and backgrounds\n\nAll overrides require `!important` since they compete with Connect's own Tailwind utility classes.\n\nThe `data-document-type` attribute selector is critical \u2014 it scopes your styles to only your editor type, preventing them from leaking into other editors in the same Connect instance.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:26.000Z"
    }
  },
